main event: A pilot spotted one or two white, fast-moving objects over Louisville, Kentucky on June 30, 1956.
interesting points: The objects appeared to have a 'licking motion' and were estimated to be traveling very fast.
The observer was an airline pilot with considerable experience identifying aircraft in flight, and stated this was definitely not a conventional aircraft.
The objects slowed down, hovered, and then accelerated and disappeared from sight.
The Air Force concluded the sighting was possibly caused by aircraft known to be in the area at the time.
sighted object: one or two white, fast-moving objects
